            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SUPPLIES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The Bergen Health Trust shall build stage 2 of the new Child and Youth Hospital (BUS2) at Haukeland University Hospital. The construction project shall be executed as divided contracts administered by the contracting authority.</P>
               <P>The project has a combined gross area of approx. 50.100 m<FT TYPE="SUP">2</FT>, and the basal area of the lowest floor (U3) is approx. 7.500 m<FT TYPE="SUP">2</FT>. The building contains three sub floors/base floors and four tangents (blocks) in varying size and height, from plan 01 to plan 06 where plan 01 also has a vestibule on the entry plan. On plan U1 there is also a parking facility.</P>
               <P>The K604 contract consists primarily of:</P>
               <P>Rigging and operation, equipped machine for thermal washing and disinfection of beds, mattresses, duvets and pillows. Also cabinet washing machines. Further information is in the attachments to the tender documentation.</P>
